---
description: FRC Code Scout — rubric-based team code analysis environment
alwaysApply: true
---

This repo scores FRC/FTC team code against an 8-dimension rubric. Full agent instructions
are in `AGENTS.md` at the repo root — read it. Key points:

- The rubric is `knowledge/rubric/rubric.md`. Score what's USED, not present — confirm every
  ast-grep/filesystem candidate by opening the cited files.
- Two jobs: analyze one team (`scripts/score_rubric.sh` + confirm + report) and build/refresh
  the corpus (`scripts/clone_corpus.sh`, `scripts/discover_repos.sh`, `scripts/build_index.sh`).
- Structural search uses ast-grep with rules in `rules/` and `sgconfig.yml`.
- Set `SCOUT_DATA` to a local disk path; never download onto a synced/mounted folder.
- Worked example: `knowledge/examples/patribots-four-year-scoring.md`.
